$\begin{align}
f(-x)&=\dfrac{3}{(-x)^2+2}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{3}{x^2+2}
\\\\
&=f(x)
\end{align}$

$\begin{align}
f(-x)&=\dfrac{1}{4-(-x)^2}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{1}{4-x^2}
\\\\
&=f(x)
\end{align}$

$\begin{align}
f(-x)&=\dfrac{(-x)}{(-x)^2+1}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{-x}{x^2+1}
\\\\
&=-\left(\dfrac{x}{x^2+1}\right)
\\\\
&=-f(x)
\end{align}$

$\begin{align}
f(-x)&=2^{(-x)+3}
\\\\
&=2^{-x}\cdot2^3
\\\\
&=\dfrac{8}{2^x}
\end{align}$

This expression isn't equivalent to $f(x)=2^{x+3}$ or to $-f(x)=-2^{x+3}$.

$\begin{align}
f(-x)&=\dfrac{(-x)^3}{(-x)+1}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{(-1)^3 \cdot x^3}{1-x}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{-x^3}{1-x}
\end{align}$

This expression isn't equivalent to $f(x)=\dfrac{x^3}{x+1}$ or to $-f(x)=\dfrac{-x^3}{x+1}$.
